                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-4-defend107 t18230910-4-deflabel17"></join>, for fourteen months. Having missed papers of halfpence, I got up at half-past six o'clock yesterday morning, and put a private mark on a pile of halfpence, on a shelf behind the counter. He slept in the house, and came down soon after six. I placed myself where I could not be seen, and saw him take one paper off the pite; I came out directly; he was then in the shop, but not behind the counter. About nine o'clock I sent for a constable, and told him I suspected him; he said he had nothing about him but what was his own. The five shilling paper was found in his pocket, with my mark on it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PRENDERGAST. Q. I believe he bore a good character - A. Yes.</p>
